Since n ≡ 2 (mod 7), we have n+2 ≡ 4, n+4 ≡ 6, n+6 ≡ 1 (mod 7). Thus (n+2)(n+4)(n+6) ≡ 4·6·1 = 24 ≡ 3 (mod 7). 
\boxed{3}

SUMMARY: The remainder is 3.

